Neue Ausstellung im @museumulm: TRANSHUMAN - von der Prothetik zum Cyborg. 
Der Ulmer Flugpionier und Tüftler Berblinger hat auch Prothesen erfunden - zum Jubiläumsjahr lotet die Ausstellung deshalb aus, wie die Möglichkeiten des menschlichen Körpers in Kunst und Technik optimiert und erweitert werden. Spannende Fragen von Prothesen als Kunstwerken bis zur Legitimität technischer Erweiterung der menschlichen Sinne - einfach reinschauen, und sich sein eigenes Bild machen! 😉😄

node.text:
Fimaro - find material resources online

Fimaro is the result of our Bachelor thesis. A prototyped concept of a platform for digital preparation of school lessons. The platform is especially aimed at teachers with little affinity for technology and is intended to make the entry into digital teaching as easy as possible.
___________________

With the help of Fimaro, teachers can easily scan a book page or a worksheet with the camera of their tablet or smartphone to find suitable teaching content. For this we implemented an image recognition and an intelligent search algorithm. This combination can search for teaching materials such as quizzes, videos, audio content, interactive tasks or augmented reality content in our database and in the web. Therefore the text on the page will be recognised and then be checked for key words to compare these with the associated curriculum. The teacher can then link the provided content to the previously scanned page in the book (or worksheet) to give access to the students in his classroom.

Students can then access this content using their smartphone or tablet by scanning the relevant page with the Fimaro student application. Here the contents are displayed in 
Augmented Reality on the book and can then be played or edited. This offers a new level of interaction with the learning content as well as digital technology.
By making learning exciting, we engage students to deal deeply with the content to improve learning naturally.

#bachelorthesis #design #designstudy #designstudent #hfg #hfggmuend #hfgiot #uxdesign #uxd #ui_ux #design #designthinking

Instagram-Takeover 001

Urbanes Alltagsleben und Elektromobilität, geht das? 
Josh Cornau und Felix Hirner beantworten diese Frage in ihrer Bachelorthesis an der HfG Schwäbisch Gmünd – mit der nutzerzentrierten E-Mobilitäts-Vermittlung @edison.emobility

Edison besteht aus einer Mobile-App mit Fahrsimulation inklusive einem Verzeichnis von Ladestationen sowie einer Webapplikation. Interaktiv finden Nutzer heraus, wie sich ihr Alltag verändern würde, wenn sie auf ein E-Fahrzeug umsteigen.
___

Urban daily life and electric mobility, is that possible? Josh Cornau and Felix Hirner answer this question in their bachelor thesis at the HfG Schwäbisch Gmünd – with the user-centered e-mobility provision @edison.emobility

Edison consists of a mobile app with driving simulation including a directory of charging stations, as well as a a web application. Interactively, users find out how their daily life would change if they switched to an e-vehicle.
___

How does a compact shaving solution look like without sacrificing the user experience of a normal razor? What feelings are asociated with shaving? Are they gender specific? Is it possible to maintain or even magnify this feeling while shrinking the size of the product? Our semester project of the first semester tried to respond to these and other questions. The models demonstrate the result of our design studies for female users. This project was made with @k_hne as a team.

Yeah, ich bin dabei - im ersten Kompendium zur Szenografie, erschienen beim Verlag av edition •
Was ist Szenografie? Von Szenografie ist die Rede, wenn Räume besonders gestaltet sind: Wenn eine Ausstellung im Museum nicht nur Objekte in die Vitrine stellt, sondern ganze Szenen zeigt. Wenn im Showroom eine Fantasiewelt erschaffen wird, die eine besondere Atmosphäre erzeugt. Wenn die neuesten Produkte auf Messen vorgestellt werden. Und wenn Geschichte in Gedenkstätten begreifbar wird. •

FARMI . A guide to find and manage your perfect Home Gardening system . 
A project I did with @nikolajohn_  and @aileen_onme under instruction of @domi_witzke 🌱

Something has changed since 2019: Facing Overpopulation, for the first time in history, more people are starting to live in cities rather than in rural areas. 
Every day, millions of trucks travel billions of kilometers to supply people living in cities with fresh produce. Yet, this phenomenon raises the question if it would be more sustainable to grow part of these products at home. But how could this be possible with such limited space a city provides? And how are cities able to produce enough food for themselves? 
People are getting more and more interested in sustainability and a more conscious way life, but they often lack the motivation or resources to change their eating habits.

So how can we as designers give them a transparent and informative platform to 
improve their health long-term and make 
them more independent while supporting 
their home gardening experience?

Da sich der Semes­ter­be­ginn für das Sommersemester 2020 um fünf Wochen nach hinten verschiebt, ergeben sich folgende Ände­rungen:

Die inter­na­tio­nale Semi­nar­woche entfällt dieses Semester und an einzelnen Brücken­tagen findet Unter­richt statt. Insge­samt verlän­gert sich das Semester um zwei Wochen. Somit wird gewährleistet, dass der Studi­en­be­trieb nur eine Woche und zwei Tage kürzer ist als ursprüng­lich geplant. Über weitere mögliche Ände­rungen halten wir euch auf dem Laufenenden.

Ulmer Hocker / Laborwoche 2019 #hfggmuendlaborwoche .
